		<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://julian.tosh.us/2011/01/junk-mail-reporting-parnership-program/" title="Permalink to Junk Mail Reporting Parnership Program" rel="bookmark">Junk Mail Reporting Parnership Program</a></h1>
                    <div class="entry-content">
                <p>I&#8217;ve always had issues sending email to MSN accounts from my Linode &#8211; getting bounces with the dreaded Blacklist 550-SC001 error message. </p>
<p>Well I apparently have broken through this wall having enrolled in the <a href="https://support.msn.com/eform.aspx?productKey=edfsjmrpp&#038;ct=eformts" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','http://support.msn.com']);">Junk Mail Reporting Partnership Program</a> at Microsoft. It&#8217;s basically a contract that identifies your SMTP servers, a reporting email contact address you maintain, and a promise to respond to opt-out requests.</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s my welcome message:<br />
<a href="http://julian.tosh.us/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/JMRPP.png" ><img src="http://julian.tosh.us/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/JMRPP-294x300.png" alt="Junk Mail Reporting Partnership Program Welcome Message" title="JMRPP" width="294" height="300" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-60" /></a></p>
