    		<div id="post-28" class="post-28 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized">
		<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://julian.tosh.us/2010/06/gmail-sendas-feature-might-put-your-organization-at-risk/" title="Permalink to Gmail SendAs feature might put your organization at risk" rel="bookmark">Gmail SendAs feature might put your organization at risk</a></h1>
                    <div class="entry-content">
                <p>Google&#8217;s Gmail product has a feature that allows you to send mail from any account for which you have control. If you are an employee of an organization where you have access to any email account, you can link your Gmail account to this email address simply by sending a verification email from Gmail.</p>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div>
